{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f3625887-0c6f-4bbd-9620-4c72a09c30c9","content":"Yes, you'll run into **framework compatibility issues**. MSTest v3 (the `MSTest` meta-package 3.x) requires:\n\n- **.NET 6.0+** or **.NET Framework 4.6.2+** (with some caveats)\n- It **drops support for `netcoreapp3.1` and `net5.0`** — both are out-of-support TFMs.\n\n### Your problematic targets:\n\n| TFM | Issue |\n|-----|-------|\n| `netcoreapp3.1` | ❌ Not supported by MSTest v3 |\n| `net5.0` | ❌ Not supported by MSTest v3 |\n| `net462` | ✅ Supported |\n\n### To migrate successfully, you'd need to:\n\n1. Replace `netcoreapp3.1` and `net5.0` with supported TFMs (e.g., `net6.0`, `net8.0`).\n2. Replace the individual package references with the unified `MSTest` package:\n\n```xml\n<PackageReference Include=\"MSTest\" Version=\"3.x.x\" />\n```\n\nIf you must keep those older TFMs, you'll need to stay on MSTest v2 or conditionally multi-target with different package versions (which gets complex). Would you like help with the migration?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"da1a1951-948b-4ebc-a4e0-e9599e133577","outputTokens":325,"requestId":"8431:37AAD:24280FB:27E34C8:6A0AD9A4"},"id":"824d09c0-1040-456d-b24c-147c3eb621ec","timestamp":"2026-05-18T09:19:44.291Z","parentId":"92bd375a-adec-41e7-a833-b998f62a26cc"}
